title: Vice President, National Homeland Security Coalition
description: The National Homeland Security Coalition, in collaboration with the National Homeland Security Association, formerly the National Urban Area Security Initiative (UASI) Homeland Security Association. the purpose of the Coalition is to conduct research, provide education, information and outreach on behalf of the Nations homeland security organizations. Our principle membership is the original 64 Urban Areas that were designated as being the most at-risk areas for a terrorist attack. With over one half of the Urban Areas being de-funded by DHS/FEMA in FFY2011, the National Homeland Security Coalition is working with our congressional delegations, municipal and private sector lobbyists, and other homeland security professionals to educate them about the risks and increased vulnerabilities associated with not funding critical grant programs. It remains the Coalition's perspective without ongoing financial sustainment by FEMA current capabilities will degrade over time creating significant gaps in our ability to mitigate against, prepare for, respond to and recover from both man made and natural disasters.
name: David Azuelo
